body:
No need to have multiple parameters to reproduce this issue.
You may have only one.
```
@Parent(
  params = {
    @Child(value = "Let's put here a really long string to demonstrate the issue. Really long.")
  }
)
public class Test {}
```

Is this issue fixed? I'm still seeing inconsistencies in the following scenario:
```java
@Parent({
  @Child(value = "Let's put here a really long string to demonstrate the issue. Really long.")
})
public class Test {}
```
`'@' has incorrect indentation level 2, expected level should be 4.`

---

This is formatted correctly, though:
```java
@Parent(
    value = {
      @Child(value = "Let's put here a really long string to demonstrate the issue. Really long.")
    })
public class Test {}
```
